Police are investigating after four cars were torched in the early hours of Tuesday at UCT&#x2019;s lower campus.The university confirmed the cars, parked in Chapel Road behind the Baxter residence, were set alight at about 2am.UCT has condemned the incident, which follows that at CPUT&apos;s Bellville campus on Monday, when six cars were torched.CPUT Fees Must Fall activists have distanced themselves from the attacks, and said their cause for free education had been hijacked by a &quot;third force&quot;.